      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantities of interest must directly correspond to the hemolysis index metric used in the clinical acceptance criterion, with traceability from model output to regulatory submission metric.",
      "rationale": "Model outputs the normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) which maps to the clinical metric. Traceability documentation is present but does not cover all edge-case operating points in the VAD envelope. Achieved level 4 falls one grade short of required level 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activities must be conducted on geometries and operating conditions representative of the specific VAD COU, not generic pump benchmarks.",
      "rationale": "Validation was conducted primarily on the FDA generic centrifugal pump benchmark geometry. Device-specific geometry validation is absent. The gap between achieved level 3 and required level 5 represents the most critical credibility deficit in this assessment."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative convergence, round-off error, and solver-specific numerical diffusion must be characterized and demonstrated to be negligible relative to hemolysis prediction uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "Numerical solver error has not been formally assessed. Residual convergence criteria are reported but no systematic study of solver-induced error in hemolysis transport has been performed. Flagged as epistemic gap at MRL 5."
    },
    {
