      "acceptanceCriteria": "Documented evidence that model users have followed prescribed simulation protocols and that analyst-to-analyst variability has been characterized for hemolysis predictions.",
      "rationale": "No inter-analyst variability study has been conducted. Simulation protocols exist but compliance verification is absent. Use error remains an unquantified epistemic gap."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The power-law hemolysis model and turbulence closure must be justified as appropriate for the specific shear stress regimes encountered in the VAD, with sensitivity analysis on model form assumptions.",
      "rationale": "The Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law model is used without formal justification of its applicability to the VAD shear regime. Turbulence model selection (SST k-omega) has not been validated against DNS data for rotating pump geometries. Model form error is the largest epistemic gap."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All model input parameters including blood viscosity, density, hemolysis model constants, and boundary condition values must be characterized with probability distributions for Monte Carlo UQ.",
      "rationale": "Monte Carlo UQ was performed but only 4 of 12 input parameters were treated as uncertain. Hemolysis model constants were held fixed at literature values without uncertainty characterization. Input uncertainty coverage is insufficient for MRL 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental samples must be characterized for geometric conformance to nominal design, with manufacturing variability documented and propagated through the simulation validation comparison.",
      "rationale": "Test pump samples were not geometrically characterized post-manufacture. Surface roughness and impeller clearance variability are unquantified. Sample characterization has not been performed, representing a complete gap at MRL 5."
    },
